The Ukrainian government on Sunday said eight Russian missiles have destroyed the airport in Vinnytsia in central Ukraine. Ukraine’s Minister of Foreign Affairs Dmytro Kuleba, disclosed this while calling the Russian President, Vladimir Putin’s action as cowardly and barbaric. Kuleba explained that Putin’s bombardment of civilians was cowardly and barbaric. In a tweet, the Minister urged foreign countries to impose a no-fly zone over Ukraine. The minister described the bombardment as Russian terrorism. He wrote: “Eight Russian cruise missiles hit Vinnytsia, a large city far from the frontline. “Putin continues his cowardly and barbaric missile strikes, air bombardment of civilians. “Help us close the sky and save lives! Provide air and missile defense, combat aircraft! Stop Russian terrorism!”